WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:02.812
<i>My name is Danny McNamara.</i>

00:02.836 --> 00:04.236
<i>When I left the FBI, I thought</i>

00:04.305 --> 00:06.425
<i>my crime-fighting days were
over, but then I learned</i>

00:06.474 --> 00:08.452
<i>that terrorist Karim Farouk
was on the hunt for Cleopatra,</i>

00:08.476 --> 00:10.576
<i>one of the world's
most valuable treasures,</i>

00:10.644 --> 00:12.478
<i>lost for over 2,000 years,</i>

00:12.546 --> 00:14.947
<i>to use her as part
of a massive terror attack.</i>

00:15.016 --> 00:16.335
<i>To find him, I needed some help,</i>

00:16.384 --> 00:18.917
<i>so I went to Lexi Vaziri,
a thief.</i>

00:18.986 --> 00:21.620
<i>Excuse me, a master thief.</i>

00:21.689 --> 00:23.756
<i>And my father
was killed by Farouk.</i>

00:23.824 --> 00:26.358
<i>Lexi and I have
a complicated past.</i>

00:26.427 --> 00:29.695
<i>He wants to bring Farouk to
justice, I want revenge.</i>

00:29.764 --> 00:31.864
<i>Also, there's a mysterious group</i>

00:31.932 --> 00:33.599
<i>who want Cleopatra
as much as we do.</i>

00:33.667 --> 00:36.301
<i>We're not sure
whether they're good or bad,</i>

00:36.370 --> 00:37.848
<i>but the one thing
we all agree on...</i>

00:37.872 --> 00:39.671
<i>Is that we need
to find Cleopatra...</i>

00:41.275 --> 00:44.376
<i>Before Farouk does.</i>

00:44.445 --> 00:46.311
<i>Previously on</i>
Blood and Treasure...

00:46.380 --> 00:49.114
<i>The Nazis believed
that some sacred objects</i>

00:49.183 --> 00:50.482
held actual power.

00:50.551 --> 00:52.684
<i>Farouk left everything
from Cleopatra's tomb,</i>

00:52.753 --> 00:55.554
<i>but what did he take?
Antony's sarcophagus.</i>

00:55.623 --> 00:58.791
<i>What if he wants to reunite
Cleopatra with Antony,</i>

00:58.859 --> 01:01.794
turn an artifact into a
weapon of mass destruction?

01:01.862 --> 01:03.862
I am Captain Bruno Fabi
of the Carabinieri...

01:03.931 --> 01:05.397
art and antiquities crimes.

01:05.465 --> 01:06.732
What's this?

01:06.801 --> 01:08.133
The medallion says "Serapis,"

01:08.202 --> 01:09.468
an ancient deity that had

01:09.537 --> 01:11.214
<i>a cult following
in the years of Cleopatra.</i>

01:11.238 --> 01:13.739
<i>They must be her protectors.</i>

01:13.808 --> 01:14.973
Doctor, this is a dead end.

01:15.042 --> 01:17.242
No, Max, this is a door.

01:17.311 --> 01:18.722
"All those who disturb
the sacred tomb

01:18.746 --> 01:21.013
"will come to know swift death

01:21.082 --> 01:23.715
and be cursed for all eternity."

01:23.784 --> 01:26.318
Come here.
It's good to see you, Chuck.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.153
Danny's a complicated guy.

01:28.222 --> 01:30.756
He follows rules and does
the right thing unfailingly.

01:30.825 --> 01:32.591
He's the furthest thing
from complicated.

01:32.660 --> 01:34.820
You and Danny have a lot more
in common than you think.

01:35.729 --> 01:36.995
Simon Hardwick.

01:37.064 --> 01:38.875
Guys like us should stick
together, shouldn't we,

01:38.899 --> 01:40.899
Special Agent McNamara?

01:40.968 --> 01:42.234
We find Cleopatra,

01:42.303 --> 01:43.335
<i>we'll find Farouk.</i>

01:43.404 --> 01:45.270
Cleopatra's in Germany.

01:45.339 --> 01:46.371
Well done, Omar.

01:50.311 --> 01:53.779
<i>Farouk went to a lot of
effort to get that photograph.</i>

01:53.848 --> 01:56.281
He's gonna go to wherever
it was taken.

01:58.000 --> 02:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:22.710 --> 02:24.943
Not so fast, Liebchen.

02:25.012 --> 02:28.147
Meet our guest of honor.

02:28.215 --> 02:32.084
Elke, say hello to Cleopatra,

02:32.153 --> 02:33.886
the future of the Reich.

02:33.954 --> 02:36.922
But she's dead. For now.

02:36.991 --> 02:39.057
But soon she will rise again.

02:39.126 --> 02:40.959
And the world
will have no choice

02:41.028 --> 02:42.961
but to bow to the Fatherland.

02:43.030 --> 02:44.596
Ah.

02:44.665 --> 02:47.599
Heinz, everybody, please,
please join us.

02:47.668 --> 02:51.803
We must commemorate this moment
of Nazi victory.

02:59.580 --> 03:00.620
Air raid! Colonel Steiner!

03:02.917 --> 03:07.252
Colonel Steiner, get Cleopatra
safely to our alternate site

03:07.321 --> 03:08.921
and continue with the project.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.656
We shall protect her
with our lives.

03:10.724 --> 03:12.724
Heinz, assemble the men.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.026
Yes, Herr Colonel.

03:14.094 --> 03:15.627
Bring up the truck now. Move!

03:49.730 --> 03:51.496
Nazis.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.232
They sure love their castles.

03:53.300 --> 03:55.133
They were all about nostalgia

03:55.202 --> 03:57.469
for a storybook world
that never actually existed.

03:57.538 --> 03:59.071
So they were angry
Ren fair nerds.

03:59.139 --> 04:01.640
Genocidally angry
Ren fair nerds, yeah.

04:01.709 --> 04:04.476
This picture of Cleopatra
could have been taken

04:04.545 --> 04:06.411
in any of a hundred
different castles.

04:06.480 --> 04:08.046
But I e-mailed
an intel analyst friend

04:08.249 --> 04:11.984
from my FBI days who now
consults at a video game studio.

04:12.052 --> 04:13.412
He's working
on a World War II game

04:13.454 --> 04:15.487
that has a whole level
in a Nazi castle.

04:15.556 --> 04:17.488
He sent tons of research
we can look at,

04:17.558 --> 04:19.024
try to narrow things down. Good,

04:19.093 --> 04:20.570
because Farouk's heading there,
wherever "there" is,

04:20.594 --> 04:22.234
and I've got a bullet
with his name on it.

04:23.230 --> 04:25.364
Metaphorically speaking,
of course.

04:27.268 --> 04:29.901
Chuck. You look...

04:29.970 --> 04:31.169
awful.

04:31.238 --> 04:33.972
What a pleasant welcome
from a guest in my own home.

04:34.041 --> 04:35.674
Irish flu.

04:35.743 --> 04:37.175
I had to end class early.

04:37.244 --> 04:39.344
Are you still hungover?

04:39.413 --> 04:41.558
Well, yeah,
I can't drink like I used to.

04:41.582 --> 04:44.416
Chuck, you drink wine
literally every day at work.

04:44.485 --> 04:47.519
Ah, yes, but technically
that is not wine.

04:47.588 --> 04:49.187
When did you guys get so chummy?

04:49.256 --> 04:52.357
Eh, now that I've gotten
to know your girlfriend...

04:52.426 --> 04:53.603
Not his girlfriend.
She's not my girlfriend.

04:53.627 --> 04:58.630
Uh-huh. I can see
that my previous doubt was

04:58.699 --> 05:00.732
a little extreme. Doubts?

05:00.801 --> 05:01.881
You said she was the devil.

05:01.935 --> 05:03.201
Aw, that was before

05:03.270 --> 05:07.039
we bonded over making fun
of you, actually.

05:07.107 --> 05:09.908
I learned all sorts
of interesting things.

05:09.977 --> 05:11.321
Uh... don't worry, nothing

05:11.345 --> 05:12.711
that you said during confession.

05:12.780 --> 05:16.048
And yet, still so much
to be embarrassed about.

05:18.552 --> 05:21.920
Is, uh, is that a picture
of a bunch of Nazis posing

05:21.989 --> 05:23.199
in front of the coffin
of Cleopatra in a castle?

05:23.223 --> 05:24.990
Yeah, 'cause that seems

05:25.059 --> 05:26.958
like that's probably a big deal.

05:27.061 --> 05:28.994
Right? Like,
historically speaking?

05:29.063 --> 05:32.798
Big enough deal that Farouk
killed somebody to get it.

05:35.169 --> 05:38.070
Inspector Karlsson,
I got your message.

05:38.138 --> 05:40.639
It was conspicuously brief,
even for you.

05:40.708 --> 05:42.074
I didn't want to give
too much away

05:42.142 --> 05:44.843
over a non-secure phone line.

05:44.912 --> 05:46.752
Don't tell me that
you're buying into this idea

05:46.814 --> 05:48.513
that Farouk has
a mole somewhere.

05:48.582 --> 05:49.981
Conspiracies...

05:50.050 --> 05:52.362
People tend to see them in the
face of inexplicable tragedy.

05:52.386 --> 05:55.120
There's nothing inexplicable
about it, Captain Fabi.

05:55.189 --> 05:57.255
Asim Masood told Danny
he thought Farouk had a mole

05:57.324 --> 05:59.524
in Egyptian intelligence,
and now he's dead.

05:59.593 --> 06:01.626
At least he didn't die in vain.

06:01.695 --> 06:02.972
You found something
in the evidence

06:02.996 --> 06:04.029
from Farouk's safe house

06:04.098 --> 06:05.430
that Danny and Lexi found?

06:05.499 --> 06:06.965
Yeah, I think so.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.934
Communications with this man,

06:09.002 --> 06:10.168
Taj bin Yusef.

06:10.237 --> 06:12.537
He ran finances
for Farouk's organization.

06:12.606 --> 06:14.539
They disappeared
at the same time.

06:14.608 --> 06:16.007
And he appears to be back.

06:16.076 --> 06:17.843
And he may have Antony.

06:17.911 --> 06:20.278
Where? Tripoli.

06:20.347 --> 06:22.592
I'm sending over the information
to Libyan authorities right now.

06:22.616 --> 06:25.851
Well done, Agent Karlsson.

06:25.919 --> 06:29.054
Let me know if the Libyans
find anything.

06:35.028 --> 06:36.561
<i>Pronto.</i>

06:41.268 --> 06:43.635
Guys, check it out.

06:43.704 --> 06:46.071
I think I found our castle.

06:46.140 --> 06:49.341
Castle Schädelberg,
near the Austrian border.

06:49.410 --> 06:52.911
Nazis did major reconstruction,
but research says

06:52.980 --> 06:55.313
it was just to stabilize
the castle.

06:55.382 --> 06:56.915
It's sitting on bedrock
in an area

06:56.984 --> 06:58.717
not known for seismic activity.

06:58.786 --> 07:01.186
This is a lot of buildup.
Better be worth it.

07:01.255 --> 07:02.821
The castle was under the purview

07:02.890 --> 07:05.991
of the Institute
for Occult Warfare.

07:06.059 --> 07:09.861
Okay. We might actually be
getting somewhere. That...

07:09.930 --> 07:12.364
looks appropriately ominous.

07:12.399 --> 07:15.600
Doing construction for stability
is a great excuse

07:15.636 --> 07:17.402
if you're trying to hide
from the world

07:17.471 --> 07:19.871
you're building a resting place
for Cleopatra.

07:19.940 --> 07:21.740
Sounds like it was
worth the buildup.

07:21.809 --> 07:23.942
Whose side are you on? Mine.

07:24.011 --> 07:25.911
Wh-When did that start
being a question?

07:25.979 --> 07:27.345
Look, Reece's jet's on standby.

07:27.414 --> 07:29.915
We can be there
before nightfall.

07:29.983 --> 07:32.851
Want to come with,
for old times?

07:32.920 --> 07:34.519
No.

07:34.588 --> 07:38.356
No. Last thing I need
is a flight over Macho Grande

07:38.425 --> 07:39.591
with you two.

07:39.660 --> 07:41.026
Where's Macho Grande?

07:41.094 --> 07:42.594
Nowhere near where we're going.

07:42.663 --> 07:44.429
Chuck's just bad at geography.

07:44.498 --> 07:47.065
And yet I always know
the lay of the land.

07:47.134 --> 07:49.868
Have fun storming the castle!

07:54.875 --> 07:56.808
Guten Tag.

08:01.014 --> 08:03.482
Of course. How may I help you?

08:03.550 --> 08:05.717
Are you the girl
in this photograph?

08:08.789 --> 08:10.121
Where did you get this?

08:10.190 --> 08:11.823
Uh, don't be alarmed.

08:11.892 --> 08:15.594
I'm a doctoral student
working on a research paper

08:15.662 --> 08:18.497
about Egyptian antiquities
during the Second World War.

08:18.565 --> 08:23.134
It was a long time ago,
but, yes, that's me.

08:23.203 --> 08:25.604
And-and that is my grandfather.

08:25.672 --> 08:29.441
Ah. Anything you can tell me
about where this was taken

08:29.510 --> 08:31.142
would be a great help.

08:31.211 --> 08:34.279
Well, I-I, I don't get
many visitors these days,

08:34.347 --> 08:36.448
but please come in.

08:37.551 --> 08:40.118
I may have some other photos

08:40.187 --> 08:43.188
that would help
with your article.

08:43.256 --> 08:46.191
How do you take your tea?

08:46.260 --> 08:49.027
I will not be having any tea.

09:08.949 --> 09:10.882
It's too late. Antony's gone.

09:10.951 --> 09:12.284
Over here!

09:16.523 --> 09:18.356
Max Najjar?

09:33.307 --> 09:34.673
Fabi?

09:34.741 --> 09:36.007
Max.

09:36.076 --> 09:37.842
How'd you find me?

09:37.911 --> 09:39.644
The Brotherhood
has been looking for you,

09:39.713 --> 09:41.212
ever since the attack
on the pyramid.

09:41.281 --> 09:44.449
We never leave
one of our own behind.

09:44.518 --> 09:46.262
One of Farouk's safe houses
was taken down yesterday.

09:46.286 --> 09:47.286
Intel led us here.

09:48.755 --> 09:50.255
Thank you for saving me.

09:50.324 --> 09:51.556
Tell me, Max.

09:51.625 --> 09:53.725
Everyone else was killed
in the explosion.

09:53.794 --> 09:55.760
How did you survive?

09:55.829 --> 09:58.063
It was a miracle.

09:59.566 --> 10:01.099
Praise God.

10:01.168 --> 10:02.834
And the terrorists
who saved you.

10:02.903 --> 10:06.705
What? They didn't save me.
They kidnapped me.

10:06.773 --> 10:08.206
They tortured me.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.719
The Brotherhood suspected
as much at first.

10:09.743 --> 10:12.277
Imagine our surprise
when we discovered

10:12.346 --> 10:14.045
the payments you took.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.880
What, what payments?

10:15.949 --> 10:17.716
Don't lie to me, Max.

10:17.784 --> 10:20.585
Farouk paid you to tell him
where to find Cleopatra.

10:20.654 --> 10:22.754
And when she wasn't there,
you must have

10:22.823 --> 10:24.189
realized they would kill you.

10:24.257 --> 10:27.559
So you offered to inform
on the Brotherhood to Farouk.

10:27.628 --> 10:29.894
I-I would never betray
the Brotherhood.

10:29.963 --> 10:32.764
Where did they take Antony?

10:32.833 --> 10:34.566
Why do they want Cleopatra?

10:34.635 --> 10:35.635
I don't know.

10:54.182 --> 10:55.782
If you want to hang back here,

10:55.851 --> 10:57.484
let me lead, it's cool.

10:57.552 --> 11:00.420
Seeing as it's your first time
casing a joint.

11:00.489 --> 11:02.589
Just, when us good guys do it,

11:02.658 --> 11:04.257
it's called
"surveillance." Yeah...

11:04.359 --> 11:05.792
not exactly the same thing.

11:08.363 --> 11:10.130
Welcome.

11:10.198 --> 11:13.266
I am your guide
through this beautiful castle.

11:13.335 --> 11:15.468
Unfortunately, we are
still waiting for two persons,

11:15.537 --> 11:17.771
- but I think...
- Hi.

11:17.839 --> 11:19.973
We're here for the 4:00 tour.

11:20.042 --> 11:21.808
Mr. and Mrs. McNamara?

11:21.877 --> 11:24.277
That's us. Great.

11:26.348 --> 11:28.782
Took your name, did I?

11:28.850 --> 11:30.183
Well, first rule
of surveillance,

11:30.252 --> 11:31.451
have a good cover story.

11:31.520 --> 11:33.086
We're newlyweds. Hmm.

11:33.155 --> 11:35.088
Was that a Southern accent?
Oh, darling.

11:35.157 --> 11:37.257
I've got a whole character
and back story worked out.

11:37.326 --> 11:38.326
Excuse me?

11:38.360 --> 11:39.993
You're so beautiful.

11:40.062 --> 11:41.695
You're such a beautiful couple.

11:41.763 --> 11:44.030
Shall I take a photo of you
in front of the staircase?

11:44.099 --> 11:46.833
Uh, we're good. Thanks.

11:46.902 --> 11:49.602
Okay. L-Let's start the tour.

11:52.040 --> 11:53.673
Never let anyone
take a picture of you.

11:53.742 --> 11:55.942
After you, Mr. McNamara.

11:56.011 --> 11:57.811
Oh, wow.

11:57.879 --> 12:00.046
As you can see on your maps,

12:00.115 --> 12:01.982
this dining room

12:02.050 --> 12:05.318
comes right after
the <i> Ruhmeshalle,</i>

12:05.387 --> 12:07.120
the Great Hall... Excuse me.

12:07.189 --> 12:09.990
Yes? I can listen to medieval
architectural history

12:10.058 --> 12:12.726
all day, it is fascinating.

12:12.794 --> 12:15.495
But my husband here is kind
of a World War II buff.

12:15.564 --> 12:17.731
Guilty as charged.

12:17.799 --> 12:19.699
I do like 'em nerdy.

12:21.303 --> 12:22.880
So could we skip the
lord and peasant stuff

12:22.904 --> 12:24.371
and maybe cut
straight to the Nazis?

12:24.439 --> 12:26.673
If y'all don't mind?

12:26.742 --> 12:28.341
Did they make any
changes to the castle?

12:28.410 --> 12:32.178
The castle's history is
over 700 years old, and...

12:32.247 --> 12:35.415
that dark era
was barely ten years.

12:35.484 --> 12:37.417
But in those ten years,

12:37.486 --> 12:39.919
wh-what specific changes
did they make?

12:39.988 --> 12:42.555
When the war ended,
we Germans promptly removed

12:42.624 --> 12:44.224
all Nazi iconography.

12:44.292 --> 12:46.037
The castle now maintains
much of the original

12:46.061 --> 12:47.327
furniture and features.

12:47.396 --> 12:49.396
As I was saying,
the 13th century

12:49.464 --> 12:50.930
brought some changes.

12:50.999 --> 12:53.166
And if you follow me,
in the <i> Ruhmeshalle</i>

12:53.235 --> 12:56.603
I can show you a very
good example of this.

13:06.581 --> 13:07.747
What? What are you doing?

13:07.816 --> 13:10.717
Change of plans.
Place closes in 20 minutes.

13:10.786 --> 13:13.253
Security system only covers
the doors and windows.

13:13.321 --> 13:16.756
Okay, so we wait for
everyone to leave...

13:16.825 --> 13:19.793
take our
time to find the hidden section

13:19.861 --> 13:21.628
where Cleopatra is.

13:21.696 --> 13:24.097
You see, my apprentice,
there is still

13:24.166 --> 13:26.866
much you have to learn
in the fine art of casing.

13:26.935 --> 13:30.103
Like how to find a bigger closet?

13:30.172 --> 13:31.571
Look, it's not my fault
that people

13:31.640 --> 13:32.939
were smaller back then.

13:33.008 --> 13:34.774
Hmm. Oh.

13:34.843 --> 13:37.377
What? Oh, I see.

13:37.446 --> 13:39.612
Wha...? Oh.

13:41.783 --> 13:44.084
It was the map.
I-It's just the map.

13:46.721 --> 13:48.988
<i>Thank you for
coming, Dr. Castillo.</i>

13:49.057 --> 13:50.457
I assume you have
summoned me here

13:50.525 --> 13:53.126
because there's a break
in the investigation?

13:53.195 --> 13:55.128
Yeah.

13:55.197 --> 13:57.597
Would you be able to, um...

13:57.666 --> 13:59.599
I.D. this man?

14:02.904 --> 14:04.471
That's Max Najjar.

14:04.539 --> 14:06.306
He was killed in
the pyramid attack

14:06.374 --> 14:07.841
along with the rest of my team.

14:07.909 --> 14:09.442
You've recovered his body, then?

14:09.511 --> 14:10.677
Yes.

14:10.745 --> 14:12.679
Tripoli Police found his body.

14:12.747 --> 14:14.247
That doesn't make sense.

14:14.316 --> 14:17.117
We have reason to believe he was
working with the terrorists.

14:17.185 --> 14:18.818
They paid him for information

14:18.887 --> 14:21.287
on Cleopatra.
Max would never do that.

14:21.356 --> 14:23.356
He did.

14:23.425 --> 14:25.091
And he paid the price.

14:25.160 --> 14:27.127
He was apparently tortured
when she wasn't there

14:27.195 --> 14:29.195
and died as a result
of his injuries.

14:29.264 --> 14:31.042
The Carabinieri and I
have been going through.

14:31.066 --> 14:32.866
Max's financial records,

14:32.934 --> 14:35.268
trying to reconstruct the weeks
leading up to the attack.

14:35.337 --> 14:37.804
It would be helpful if we can
have a timeline from you.

14:37.873 --> 14:40.373
For comparison. Of course.

14:40.442 --> 14:42.542
Ever since we entered

14:42.611 --> 14:45.512
Antony and Cleopatra's tomb,
nothing has made sense.

14:47.115 --> 14:50.650
I'm beginning to think
that it is cursed.

14:55.690 --> 14:57.056
So you're sure

14:57.125 --> 14:58.658
there's no security cameras
in here?

14:58.727 --> 15:00.693
Yes. We're good.

15:00.729 --> 15:03.463
They were all at the
entrances of the building.

15:03.532 --> 15:06.299
Oh, amateurs.

15:08.470 --> 15:10.036
Uh-uh.

15:10.105 --> 15:11.838
Don't even think about it.

15:11.907 --> 15:14.374
I was admiring the jewel inlay.

15:14.442 --> 15:17.210
It was sparkling at me
