32:30.678 --> 32:31.410
Luxurious.

32:31.679 --> 32:32.444
<i>But what are the smelling?</i>

32:32.680 --> 32:33.512
Wait, it's Suave?

32:33.681 --> 32:34.446
Wow.

32:34.682 --> 32:35.480
It's Bodywash.

32:35.683 --> 32:36.683
No it's not.

32:36.917 --> 32:38.061
I can't believe this is Suave.

32:38.085 --> 32:38.650
Can I take this home?

32:38.886 --> 32:39.886
<i>Suave Body Wash.</i>

32:40.287 --> 32:42.207
<i>Fragrances as Beautiful
as Bath and Body Works.</i>

32:45.593 --> 32:48.594
Hey! A heart in my Honey Nut
Cheerios.

32:48.629 --> 32:49.728
That's special.

32:49.763 --> 32:52.564
Like a tasty Cereal that can
help lower cholesterol.

32:52.600 --> 32:54.132
Still going to eat you though.

32:54.168 --> 32:56.201
You're not that special.

32:58.305 --> 33:01.240
Ours is a proud bloodline.

33:01.275 --> 33:05.911
We hail from the battlefields to
the badlands.

33:05.946 --> 33:10.682
From the mountains and the
midtowns.

33:10.718 --> 33:15.287
From the islands to the
highlands.

33:15.322 --> 33:18.423
And directly to those who
understand...

33:18.459 --> 33:20.692
That when you get behind the
wheel.

33:20.728 --> 33:23.528
You're not just driving
a Jeep Wrangler.

33:23.564 --> 33:31.564
You're joining a family.

35:49.910 --> 35:52.911
<i>We should stay here until
we figure out our next move.</i>

35:52.980 --> 35:55.480
So, you are very <i>glücklich, ja?</i>

35:55.549 --> 35:56.948
Eh, lucky?

35:57.017 --> 35:59.684
Because of the football match,
we have been booked for months,

35:59.753 --> 36:01.319
but I just spoke with the owner.

36:01.388 --> 36:03.989
He has accepted to liberate
our last room.

36:04.057 --> 36:05.957
It's very, um...

36:06.026 --> 36:07.492
cozy, yeah?

36:07.561 --> 36:10.595
Wonderful. Thanks.

36:10.664 --> 36:12.631
<i>Gute Nacht.</i>

36:12.699 --> 36:14.433
Oh, it's Chuck.

36:14.501 --> 36:16.468
He got my text.

36:16.537 --> 36:18.870
"Interesting photo,
nothing jumps out,

36:18.939 --> 36:20.505
"but I can look
into it tomorrow.

36:20.574 --> 36:25.310
My gut tells me it has something
to do with Macho Grande."

36:25.379 --> 36:28.046
The man's obsessed with
this Macho Grande place.

36:28.115 --> 36:29.548
What's so great about it?

36:29.616 --> 36:32.717
Nothing. It's... Fine.

36:32.786 --> 36:35.520
Don't tell me. He will
next time I get him drunk.

36:35.589 --> 36:37.755
He's gonna check in the
Vatican archives tomorrow

37:13.658 --> 37:14.824
American!

37:27.071 --> 37:28.204
All right, go, go, go!

37:32.510 --> 37:34.277
On the ridge. Got 'em!

37:55.967 --> 37:57.366
All clear.

37:57.435 --> 38:00.102
We're clear!

38:00.171 --> 38:04.240
Okay, I want everyone rounded up
for questioning.

38:06.711 --> 38:09.645
Marwan, find out if anyone
here has seen our guy.

38:13.785 --> 38:16.319
Let's be very careful
with the artifacts.

38:16.387 --> 38:18.227
There's millions worth
of stolen treasure here.

38:19.858 --> 38:20.990
Agent Danny,

38:21.059 --> 38:24.427
one of the men says your
archaeologist is here.

38:26.531 --> 38:28.664
Could be our guy.

38:28.733 --> 38:30.967
Or could be a trap.

38:31.035 --> 38:32.735
Okay, nice and easy.

38:32.804 --> 38:35.571
Check for trip wires.

38:44.849 --> 38:46.148
Are you Simon Hardwick?

38:46.217 --> 38:50.486
I'm Special Agent McNamara, FBI.

38:50.555 --> 38:53.022
We're here to rescue you.

38:53.091 --> 38:55.024
It's okay.

38:55.093 --> 38:58.461
You're gonna be okay.

38:58.529 --> 39:01.197
Medic!

39:01.266 --> 39:03.032
Short, gray hair.

39:03.101 --> 39:05.668
He had these deep set
brown eyes.

39:14.445 --> 39:16.646
So he got away then?

39:16.714 --> 39:19.615
I know this is difficult,
but when we catch him,

39:19.684 --> 39:21.550
we're gonna have you to thank.

39:21.619 --> 39:23.319
How did you find me?

39:23.388 --> 39:25.988
I'm in the FBI's Arts
and Antiquities Division.

39:26.057 --> 39:27.323
British intel alerted us

39:27.392 --> 39:29.058
that an archaeologist
had been kidnapped.

39:29.127 --> 39:31.627
Meanwhile, we've been tracking
a new terrorist on the scene

39:31.696 --> 39:34.697
who's been very well funded.
Hmm.

39:34.732 --> 39:38.501
We've been able to track some of
the blood antiquities he sold.

39:38.569 --> 39:40.636
Did you get any idea
what he might be planning,

39:40.705 --> 39:41.904
or why?

39:44.075 --> 39:46.809
That's him.

39:46.878 --> 39:48.978
His name is Karim Farouk.

39:49.047 --> 39:52.048
He wants revenge,

39:52.116 --> 39:55.885
and he won't stop
until he has it.

40:00.725 --> 40:02.758
Oh, please.

40:02.827 --> 40:04.827
Dealers are such parasites.

40:04.896 --> 40:08.564
All you do is profit.
You don't create.

40:08.633 --> 40:10.833
Parasite's such a nasty word,
don't you think?

40:13.738 --> 40:14.870
<i>Grazie. Prego.</i>

40:14.939 --> 40:16.372
What I do is, uh,

40:16.441 --> 40:18.874
I create the context
for the buyer

40:18.943 --> 40:20.242
that sets an object's value.

40:22.480 --> 40:24.947
Like that necklace
you're wearing, for example.

40:25.016 --> 40:27.850
The craftsmanship's
a bit pedestrian.

40:27.919 --> 40:30.130
Probably purchased from some
mid-tier jewelry market chain,

40:30.154 --> 40:32.121
but the person who bought it
for you is special,

40:32.190 --> 40:34.890
to you, at least.

40:34.959 --> 40:37.560
Maybe someone you're
a bit in love with still,

40:37.628 --> 40:40.730
which is why,
when the chain breaks,

40:40.798 --> 40:42.631
which it's done
a number of times,

40:42.700 --> 40:45.034
you get it fixed again and again
with new links,

40:45.103 --> 40:48.371
making it unique
and priceless to you.

40:48.439 --> 40:50.940
Okay, I get it.

40:51.009 --> 40:53.020
So, what, are you only here
for the gallery opening?

40:53.044 --> 40:55.089
Why don't you join me for
dinner, and I'll tell you...

40:55.113 --> 40:56.523
Mr. Hardwick, we have
some questions for you.

40:56.547 --> 40:59.048
I'm just in the middle
of something rather important.

40:59.117 --> 41:00.449
It was nice to meet you.

41:00.518 --> 41:03.953
Uh... great.

41:04.022 --> 41:06.088
Uh, don't you have
anything better to do

41:06.157 --> 41:08.090
than bother me when
I'm working on something?

41:08.159 --> 41:09.959
Work? That did not
look like work.

41:10.028 --> 41:11.460
Well, not your kind of work.

41:11.529 --> 41:13.207
This isn't about your business,
Mr. Hardwick,

41:13.231 --> 41:14.663
this is a murder investigation.

41:14.732 --> 41:16.599
Max Najjar.

41:16.667 --> 41:17.933
I believe you knew him.

41:18.002 --> 41:21.337
Does anyone really know
anyone these days?

41:21.406 --> 41:23.172
You transferred money
into his account.

41:23.241 --> 41:25.408
Well, in that sense,
I knew him, yes, yes.

41:25.476 --> 41:27.510
Max... Najjar.

41:27.578 --> 41:29.912
Yeah, h-he was in some
financial difficulty,

41:29.981 --> 41:31.781
and he needed to make
a quick sale.

41:31.849 --> 41:34.417
How did Najjar come to work
with Karim Farouk?

41:34.485 --> 41:35.818
How the hell should I know?

41:35.887 --> 41:37.753
Let me break this down for you:

41:37.822 --> 41:40.356
There's no love lost
between me and the man

41:40.425 --> 41:42.858
who held me as a slave
and tortured me for a year.

41:42.927 --> 41:44.687
Maybe you'll also understand
that my business

41:44.729 --> 41:48.597
relies on discretion,
so the only questions I ask

41:48.666 --> 41:51.600
are to establish the provenance
of a piece for sale, that's it.

41:51.669 --> 41:54.103
We will get to the bottom of
this, with or without your help.

41:54.172 --> 41:55.671
Okay. If we find out that you've

41:55.740 --> 41:59.141
been financing terrorism,
knowingly or unknowingly,

41:59.210 --> 42:01.210
you will be treated
exactly the same as them.

42:01.279 --> 42:02.645
Right, that's good to know.

42:02.713 --> 42:05.147
You should make a change to
your plans. Italy will become

42:05.216 --> 42:07.483
a very difficult place
for you to do business.

42:07.552 --> 42:09.518
More difficult than it is now?

42:09.587 --> 42:11.654
Let's go.

42:11.722 --> 42:13.355
The Brotherhood of Serapis.

42:17.662 --> 42:20.229
Does that name
mean anything to you?

42:20.298 --> 42:21.831
What about them?

42:21.899 --> 42:24.533
There are people in this world

42:24.602 --> 42:27.036
that scare me more
than Karim Farouk.

42:27.105 --> 42:29.672
I believe Max was
working for them.

42:29.740 --> 42:32.308
He tried to sell me
this medallion he was wearing.

42:32.376 --> 42:36.745
It had three intertwined
serpents etched on the front.

42:36.814 --> 42:38.747
You want to find out
what happened to Max?

42:38.816 --> 42:40.649
You want to get
to the bottom of this?

42:40.718 --> 42:42.418
I suggest you look into them.

42:42.487 --> 42:43.919
And maybe you'll do me the favor

42:43.988 --> 42:46.522
of not putting my name
on any paperwork,

42:46.591 --> 42:49.725
because if you do,
my blood'll be on your hands.

42:54.968 --> 42:57.969
<i>We should stay here until
we figure out our next move.</i>

42:58.038 --> 43:00.539
So, you are very <i>glücklich, ja?</i>

43:00.607 --> 43:02.007
Eh, lucky?

43:02.076 --> 43:04.743
Because of the football match,
we have been booked for months,

43:04.812 --> 43:06.378
but I just spoke with the owner.

43:06.447 --> 43:09.047
He has accepted to liberate
our last room.

43:09.116 --> 43:11.016
It's very, um...

43:11.085 --> 43:12.551
cozy, yeah?

43:12.619 --> 43:15.654
Wonderful. Thanks.

43:15.723 --> 43:17.689
<i>Gute Nacht.</i>

43:17.758 --> 43:19.491
Oh, it's Chuck.

43:19.560 --> 43:21.526
He got my text.

43:21.595 --> 43:23.929
"Interesting photo,
nothing jumps out,

43:23.997 --> 43:25.564
"but I can look
into it tomorrow.

43:25.632 --> 43:30.368
My gut tells me it has something
to do with Macho Grande."

43:30.437 --> 43:33.105
The man's obsessed with
this Macho Grande place.

43:33.173 --> 43:34.606
What's so great about it?

43:34.675 --> 43:37.776
Nothing. It's... Fine.

43:37.845 --> 43:40.579
Don't tell me. He will
next time I get him drunk.

43:40.647 --> 43:43.181
He's gonna check in the
Vatican archives tomorrow

43:43.250 --> 43:45.050
and let us know
if he finds anything.

43:47.087 --> 43:49.421
Cozy.

43:51.525 --> 43:55.293
It's okay. I can take the floor.

43:55.362 --> 43:58.096
So we're pretend-divorced now?

43:58.165 --> 44:00.866
Don't trust me to share the
bed, or don't trust yourself?

44:00.934 --> 44:02.868
Just trying to keep things
uncomplicated.

44:02.936 --> 44:04.903
Don't flatter yourself.

44:04.972 --> 44:06.938
I am exhausted.

44:07.007 --> 44:08.874
I only have eyes
for this pillow.

44:08.942 --> 44:11.243
Yeah? I have had such

44:11.311 --> 44:13.678
a busy day,

44:13.747 --> 44:15.614
Climbing the big castles,

44:15.682 --> 44:18.250
chasing the angry Nazis, yeah?

44:18.318 --> 44:19.584
Yeah...

44:19.653 --> 44:22.220
the accent's not
your strongest move.

44:23.323 --> 44:25.991
What?

44:26.059 --> 44:29.060
How dare you?

44:29.129 --> 44:32.998
I'm just saying, I
have a few notes. No?

44:33.066 --> 44:35.333
I was too nice, wasn't I?

44:35.402 --> 44:39.271
You like me better when I'm bad.

44:39.339 --> 44:42.908
You like you better
when you're bad.

44:48.348 --> 44:52.250
Maybe it's time we talk about
the elephant in the room.

44:54.354 --> 44:56.955
There's barely room for us
in this room.

44:57.024 --> 44:59.090
We're gonna find Farouk again.

44:59.159 --> 45:00.826
I want to make sure

45:00.894 --> 45:02.238
we're on the same page.

45:02.262 --> 45:04.296
I know you want
to take him alive,

45:04.364 --> 45:05.964
and for the sake
of getting along,

45:06.033 --> 45:08.466
I'm happy to let you believe
that you will.

45:08.535 --> 45:11.102
Killing Farouk doesn't
necessarily stop the attack,

45:11.171 --> 45:13.271
but it does keep us
from finding out his plan.

45:13.340 --> 45:16.608
And it makes damn sure
he doesn't get away again.

45:16.677 --> 45:18.109
It gets justice for my father.

45:18.178 --> 45:20.378
Revenge isn't the same thing
as justice.

45:20.447 --> 45:21.847
Justice happens
in a court of law,

45:21.915 --> 45:23.281
in front of the whole world.

45:23.350 --> 45:26.351
I don't care that the world
gets to see it.

45:26.420 --> 45:28.386
I just want to be the one
that kills him.

45:30.023 --> 45:33.358
If this is all about revenge,

45:33.427 --> 45:37.329
even if you get what you want,

45:37.397 --> 45:40.332
you're gonna be holding on
to the anger forever.

45:42.402 --> 45:45.003
Your father wouldn't
have wanted that.

45:47.641 --> 45:49.574
You're right.

45:50.777 --> 45:53.144
You should take the floor.

46:03.290 --> 46:05.056
How'd you sleep?

46:05.125 --> 46:07.158
Fine. You?

46:07.227 --> 46:08.994
Never better.

46:11.932 --> 46:13.899
Yo, Chuck? You're on speaker.

46:13.967 --> 46:15.667
That's Danny's subtle way
of telling you

46:15.736 --> 46:17.080
not to say anything
that would embarrass him.

46:17.104 --> 46:18.436
But don't hold back
on my account.

46:18.505 --> 46:20.005
Okay.

46:20.073 --> 46:24.910
Hey, uh, I sent your code to,
uh, some of my Jesuit brothers.

46:24.978 --> 46:27.545
And, uh, I think we figured out

46:27.614 --> 46:29.514
the answer.

46:29.583 --> 46:33.018
And the answer may shake
the very foundations

46:33.086 --> 46:35.186
of Western civilization.

46:35.255 --> 46:37.055
Shh!

46:38.158 --> 46:39.235
Are you guys holding in
your laughs?

46:39.259 --> 46:40.692
'Cause I can't tell
over the phone.

46:40.761 --> 46:42.861
If I say yes,
will you tell me what it is?

46:42.930 --> 46:45.730
Sheesh. You two are a delight
this morning.

46:45.799 --> 46:50.902
Well, the Kreisau code was next
to a very specific Jesuit Bible

46:50.971 --> 46:53.204
that all of these guys
would have had.

46:53.273 --> 46:55.473
This Bible was not
there accidentally.

46:55.542 --> 46:57.309
It was the key.

46:59.780 --> 47:01.746
Nothing? Really?

47:01.815 --> 47:04.049
Nic Cage? <i> National Treasure?</i>

47:04.117 --> 47:06.751
You guys are really,
uh, draining all of the fun

47:06.820 --> 47:08.787
out of this for me,
you know that, right?

47:08.855 --> 47:13.892
Anyway, this Jesuit library had
copies of the Kreisau Bible,

47:13.961 --> 47:16.094
so we went through it.

47:16.163 --> 47:19.731
Took us a couple hours,
but we figured out the code.

47:19.800 --> 47:22.400
Now, each number corresponds
to a different letter,

47:22.469 --> 47:24.235
in reference
to a specific verse.

47:24.304 --> 47:28.173
We put it all together, and...

47:28.241 --> 47:33.945
it spelled
"Sauber-Depot, garage 18."

47:35.182 --> 47:37.115
Sauber-Depot?

47:37.184 --> 47:38.650
Sounds like
an old military base.

47:38.719 --> 47:40.085
Yeah.

47:40.153 --> 47:43.254
The Internet said that it's,
uh, an old, uh,

47:43.323 --> 47:46.358
an old Panzer repair depot
from the war.

47:46.426 --> 47:51.129
And Maps says that it's
not that far from your castle.

47:51.198 --> 47:53.765
Why would they take
Cleopatra to an army base?

47:53.834 --> 47:57.168
Well, there's not many more
secure places in the '40s

47:57.237 --> 47:59.471
than a German military base.

47:59.539 --> 48:01.373
Hey, thanks, Chuck.

48:01.441 --> 48:03.775
Hey, no problem. You know what?
We'll call it even

48:03.844 --> 48:05.443
if you can pick me up
some of those, uh,

48:05.512 --> 48:07.445
those apple pancakes they got...

48:07.514 --> 48:10.281
My God, is he a chatty one.

48:10.350 --> 48:14.352
Look, about last night...

48:14.421 --> 48:17.989
what happened or didn't...
Don't.

48:18.058 --> 48:19.657
Don't. You're you, I'm me.

48:19.726 --> 48:22.894
It's best if we accept it.

48:22.963 --> 48:25.397
Yeah.

48:25.465 --> 48:29.334
Come on. Let's go.

48:29.403 --> 48:31.803
We're actually ahead
of Farouk for once.

48:48.922 --> 48:51.723
Garage 18.

48:52.793 --> 48:54.159
Not exactly where you'd expect

48:54.227 --> 48:55.994
to find the last queen of Egypt.

48:56.063 --> 48:58.063
Maybe that's why no one has.

49:01.168 --> 49:04.335
If Cleopatra was here,
I'm guessing

49:04.404 --> 49:06.571
she wasn't here for long.

49:06.640 --> 49:09.441
These walls make no sense here.

49:09.509 --> 49:11.743
They block the whole bay

49:11.812 --> 49:14.412
and serve no structural purpose.

49:23.990 --> 49:25.290
Something behind this wall.

49:25.358 --> 49:27.292
Yeah?

49:29.362 --> 49:31.296
After you.

49:47.714 --> 49:49.414
It's a freight elevator.

49:49.483 --> 49:50.715
To where, I wonder.

49:52.152 --> 49:54.552
The Germans hid their treasure

49:54.621 --> 49:55.887
in underground vaults

49:55.956 --> 49:57.922
to protect them
from bombardment.

49:57.991 --> 49:59.791
So if they were
in enough of a hurry,

49:59.860 --> 50:01.493
they could've left Cleopatra

50:01.561 --> 50:03.294
down there.

50:03.363 --> 50:04.662
Let's find out.

50:24.926 --> 50:26.526
We'd better be careful.

50:26.595 --> 50:27.595
Yeah.

50:31.800 --> 50:33.733
Yeah.

50:42.577 --> 50:45.678
Oh, God!

50:45.747 --> 50:47.947
Yeah.

50:48.016 --> 50:49.516
Whoa.

50:53.955 --> 50:55.355
Wow.

50:55.423 --> 50:58.791
The good news is we're rich.

51:03.765 --> 51:05.465
This was melted down

51:05.534 --> 51:07.800
from the jewelry of the people
they sent to the camps.

51:07.869 --> 51:10.036
Oh.

51:13.308 --> 51:15.241
Wow.

51:15.310 --> 51:16.643
Lexi.

51:16.711 --> 51:19.579
Cleopatra was here.

51:21.683 --> 51:24.584
In the photo, this was the top
of her sarcophagus.

51:24.653 --> 51:26.886
Must have been hard
to travel with.

51:26.955 --> 51:28.321
In the rush to get out,

51:28.390 --> 51:31.324
they just pried it off
and left it.

51:32.394 --> 51:33.726
I can't believe this.

51:33.795 --> 51:35.428
Least we're getting closer.

51:35.497 --> 51:37.730
Closer? To what?

51:37.799 --> 51:39.232
Cleopatra?

51:39.301 --> 51:40.733
Farouk?

51:40.802 --> 51:42.602
What a waste.

51:42.671 --> 51:44.604
"Close" is just another word
for "nothing."

51:58.887 --> 52:01.187
You been looking for me?

52:05.060 --> 52:06.626
Who are you?

52:06.695 --> 52:08.261
One of them?

52:08.330 --> 52:10.096
One of who?

52:10.165 --> 52:11.497
Serapis.

52:11.566 --> 52:13.499
They call themselves
The Brotherhood.

52:13.568 --> 52:15.368
Does it look like
I'm one of them?

52:15.437 --> 52:17.370
Turn around.

52:17.439 --> 52:19.939
I said turn around.

52:34.456 --> 52:36.656
So, who are you?

52:38.727 --> 52:40.059
I won't ask again.

52:41.196 --> 52:43.796
Lexi Vaziri.

52:43.865 --> 52:45.465
Vaziri.

52:47.068 --> 52:49.135
Reza Vaziri's daughter.

52:49.237 --> 52:51.337
A greedy little girl
who shed her skin

52:51.406 --> 52:53.039
like a snake
to become a Westerner.

52:53.108 --> 52:54.741
Who betrayed her own people,

52:54.809 --> 52:56.209
got her father killed.

52:56.277 --> 52:57.844
I betrayed my own people?

52:57.912 --> 53:00.346
You killed hundreds of our
people, bombed the pyramids.

53:00.415 --> 53:01.859
The pyramids are nothing
but an attraction

53:01.883 --> 53:03.082
to Western tourists.

53:04.219 --> 53:07.153
A symbol of a conquered people.

53:09.224 --> 53:11.991
You didn't find Cleopatra there.

53:12.060 --> 53:14.761
You won't find her here, either.

53:16.898 --> 53:19.365
You tell me where she went,

53:19.434 --> 53:22.502
or this place becomes your tomb.

53:22.570 --> 53:25.071
I'll never tell you anything.

53:26.508 --> 53:29.442
Two men are coming.

53:29.511 --> 53:31.744
Have it your way.

53:48.129 --> 53:50.897
Thanks. We're trapped.

53:52.000 --> 53:54.534
Well, we might be able
to make it out.

53:55.837 --> 53:56.903
Up there.

53:59.240 --> 54:00.640
Right.

54:00.709 --> 54:02.742
You know, in case
this doesn't go well,

54:02.811 --> 54:06.045
I think we should talk about...
No, no, no. We are not having

54:06.114 --> 54:07.258
an "in case this doesn't
go well" conversation.

54:07.282 --> 54:08.381
Okay, but if it doesn't...

54:08.450 --> 54:09.916
We're gonna be fine.

54:09.984 --> 54:11.551
Look, when Chuck
and I were kids,

54:11.619 --> 54:13.319
we used to love
the <i> Airplane!</i> movies.

54:13.388 --> 54:14.587
Huh?

54:14.656 --> 54:16.823
Seriously? <i> Airplane!?</i>

54:16.891 --> 54:18.558
"Don't call me Shirley."

54:18.626 --> 54:21.060
Why are you telling me this?
In the movie,

54:21.129 --> 54:24.630
Macho Grande is that thing
you can't get over.

54:24.699 --> 54:27.500
Thing you hold on to even
when you should let it go.

54:32.340 --> 54:35.174
Chuck thinks
you're my Macho Grande.

54:35.243 --> 54:37.510
So, is Chuck right?

54:37.579 --> 54:40.246
Am I your Macho Grande?

54:43.485 --> 54:44.617
Danny.

54:44.686 --> 54:46.252
Danny!

54:47.655 --> 54:49.655
Danny! Hold on.

54:49.724 --> 54:51.157
Come on.

54:53.361 --> 54:55.361
Lexi!

54:56.498 --> 54:58.931
Oh, boy.

55:13.615 --> 55:16.549
Uh... little help?!

55:18.086 --> 55:20.453
